🤷🏻‍♂️

If I never work in this town again…it will have been worth it! 

I had such a blast making this song/video as an #HPPartner with my friends, family and TONS of autotune for a great cause. 

Today, @HP introduces the #HPPaysYourPTA program in which they are donating up to $3 million to PTAs. Get your school started by signing up for this unique fundraiser featuring HP Instant Ink at hp.com/pta and spread the word about your own fundraiser by creating your own Instagram Reel, using our original sound to lip sync this song and share with #HPPaysYourPTA.

And thank you to @jamey_heath_ for producing this song and making me sound like a lost distant cousin of the #backstreetboys. And for @emilybaldoni and @juanpachecojunior for loving me enough to play with me!

Directed by the amazing @mikeho_ 
Choreography by my sis @movement.with.natasha 
 
#BacktoSchool #PTA #ParentingTips #ParentsBeLike

node.text:
No one ever sees the iceberg that exists UNDER the water. The countless mistakes and awkward moments before we broadcast our lives and relationships on social media. The times we weren’t on the same page or when I was ignoring all her signs and taking on my self assigned role as the white knight by publicly claiming “my woman” via grand gesture after grand gesture. 

I feel like our culture needs to see more examples of happy marriages who have done and are doing the work (it never stops) who have made it through messy and uncomfortable times along the way. To me #goals are about imperfection and talking about the work of relationships. Showing the humanity not just the highlight reel.

The truth is, there is no such thing as a honeymoon phase: i believe it’s just a delay of the real, deep, messy, uncomfortable and confronting work of being in a relationship. Of course you can have amazing chemistry off the bat but I don’t think true lasting happiness can start until both parties are radically honest with what the other needs and wants. Work that most of us are too afraid to do for fear of either scaring away the person we are with or being scared away by them not being the perfect “idea” of who we want them to be or who society has told us they should be.

We all have stuff. We all have shit. Let’s stop pretending we don’t and embrace it. When we allow it in and stop rejecting it, that shit it becomes the fertilizer for the soil of unconditional love.

@emilybaldoni @wearemanenough

node.text:
The love for this episode has been nothing short of overwhelming for me and my dad. Having this conversation wasn’t easy but hearing from so many of you about how healing this was to listen to means the world to us. This sums up so much of this journey for me. Emotion and vulnerability meeting. Creating a safe place that allows us to expose and express our weaknesses, our mistakes; creating a closeness that allows us to embrace our humanness…together.

It’s what I hope my kids and I can always share.

It’s what I’m starting to share with my own parents, and what I’m so thankful I could share with my dad, @sambaldoni, in this episode. 

#ManEnough #TheManEnoughPodcast

node.text:
The love for this episode has been nothing short of overwhelming for me and my dad. 

Having this conversation wasn’t easy but hearing from so many of you about how healing this was to listen to means the world to us. 

This sums up so much of this journey for me. Emotion and vulnerability meeting. Creating a safe place that allows us to expose and express our weaknesses, our mistakes; creating a closeness that allows us to embrace our humanness…together.

It’s what I hope my kids and I can always share.

It’s what I’m starting to share with my own parents, and what I’m so thankful I could share with my dad, @sambaldoni, in this episode. 

#ManEnough #TheManEnoughPodcast

node.text:
This man…this human. @jamey_heath_ is one of my best friends; he’s been a mentor, a teacher, a brother, and on multiple occasions, even a backup dancer (if you know, you know 😜) to me. He is always super patient and truthful as I have stumbled and grown, over and over and over again. He’s the truest example I know of what it means when they say ‘hurt people hurt people and healed people heal people.’
 
Jamey’s story is raw, painful, honest, inspiring, and full of growth, healing, and humility. And man, I hope you’ll tune in to the new episode of The #ManEnoughPodcast and get to know the guy that I am honored to call a brother.
 
Jamey, my man, I love you.

PLEASE WATCH/LISTEN TO THIS EPISODE. This is why we make this show. 

#ManEnough

node.text:
Last night on our bedtime walk I caught this little moment of magic. 

@emilybaldoni can’t help but move her body when she feels called. When nature calls. It’s so breathtakingly beautiful on its own, but watching Maiya mimic her every action damn near brought me to tears. 

Our kids study us. They observe. They watch our every move. They take in all we say and even more so what we don’t say. They feel it all and absorb like little sponges and then copy us because we are there guides. Their teachers. Their safe places. 

If only they knew they were actually the ones teaching us. 

Their innate goodness, curiosity, and joy is just that…innate. It isn’t learned. 

We are the reasons they forget. But if we let them they will help us remember. 

Let’s never forget. Our actions today will be their actions tomorrow. 

Let’s heal while we can so we can show the next generation how to heal. 

Healed people heal people.

In this week’s #ManEnoughPodcast episode, my dear friend @rainnwilson calls our podcast “stupid.” 😂 

Not only is this man one of the funniest guys I know, but more importantly, he’s one of the most respectable men I know. And I am super grateful to have him in my life as a friend, brother, and spiritual mentor. He’s a man who genuinely cares, shows up for people, and is someone I know I can call when I’m struggling...someone who will listen, validate my humanity, and who always gives me the truth with love (and maybe a wiseass comment). 

This man is the real deal and he’s made me a better friend, husband, father, and Bahai in so many ways. 

I’m excited for you to hear more about his story, his struggles, and his commitment to being the best version of himself, while helping make our world better in the process.
 
#ManEnough

Super grateful to have my friend @jayshetty sharing his wisdom and truth on The #ManEnoughPodcast this week!

Jay is a very special soul. I don’t meet many people (especially in the self-help space) who truly live what they teach. He is everything you would think he would be and more. What I appreciate so much about Jay is that he isn’t a teacher, he’s a student. He just shares what he has learned along the way and what he is learning.

Jay is incredible at making ancient wisdom accessible to the masses and he invites us and challenges us to see that service is at the core of who we are as people, and that being of service to one another—to humanity—is the only way we will ever more forward and be truly successful as a society.

Tune in to this week’s episode for such an important, urgent, and timely reminder with all the heartache going on in the world.

What can you do today to be of service to someone else?

#ManEnough

No one ever sees the iceberg that exists UNDER the water. The countless mistakes and awkward moments before we broadcast our lives and relationships on social media. The times we weren’t on the same page or when I was ignoring all her signs and taking on my self assigned role as the white knight by publicly claiming “my woman” via grand gesture after grand gesture. 

I feel like our culture needs to see more examples of happy marriages who have done and are doing the work (it never stops) who have made it through messy and uncomfortable times along the way. To me #goals are about imperfection and talking about the work of relationships. Showing the humanity not just the highlight reel.

The truth is, there is no such thing as a honeymoon phase: i believe it’s just a delay of the real, deep, messy, uncomfortable and confronting work of being in a relationship. Of course you can have amazing chemistry off the bat but I don’t think true lasting happiness can start until both parties are radically honest with what the other needs and wants. Work that most of us are too afraid to do for fear of either scaring away the person we are with or being scared away by them not being the perfect “idea” of who we want them to be or who society has told us they should be.

We all have stuff. We all have shit. Let’s stop pretending we don’t and embrace it. When we allow it in and stop rejecting it, that shit it becomes the fertilizer for the soil of unconditional love.

@emilybaldoni @wearemanenough
